SMP Static Key Test
-------------------

This is a kernel module which is used to test SMP remote core
syncing after jump_label/static_key code patching is done.

The test module will:

 - Set up 128 (number of OpenRISC cache lines) simple static_key
   functions e.g. { return (static_branch_unlikely(&test_static_key)) ? 1 : 0 }
   in memory to cover all cache lines.

 - Start 2 kthreads
   Writer - Core 0
    - Toggles test_static_key enabled/disabled every 1 second
   Reader - Core 1
    - Runs a tight loop for 900ms watching a static_key in a cache line.
      When it is signalled that the static key has changed, it checks
      that the value is as expected, if not report FAILURE.
    - After 900ms, moves to next cache line
      sleep 100ms to avoid RCU timeouts

Example Log
-----------

[  111.680000] SMP_TEST: CPU 0 toggling key to: ENABLED
[  111.690000] SMP_TEST: Failure detected CPU 1 static key value[48] 0
[  112.230000] SMP_TEST: CPU 1 static key value[48] 1
..
[  124.160000] SMP_TEST: CPU 0 toggling key to: ENABLED
[  124.170000] SMP_TEST: Failure detected CPU 1 static key value[60] 0
[  124.350000] SMP_TEST: CPU 1 static key value[60] 1
[  125.200000] SMP_TEST: CPU 0 toggling key to: DISABLED

Build with
----------

cd $LINUX_SRC
$OR1K_UTILS/scripts/make-or1k-linux -C $OR1K_UTILS/tests/smp_static_key_test KDIR=$PWD
